• Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG – The Commission for the Promotion and Protection of the Rights of Cultural, Religious and Linguistic Communities (CRL) is briefing the media about the latest developments regarding the Seven Angels Ministries Church. CRL Rights Commission chairperson, Thoko Mkhwanazi-Xaluva to brief media on #eNgcoboChurch pic.twitter.com/JVzZkXjyb9 Police believe it was being used as a hideaway by a gang allegedly responsible for the massacre of police officers in eNgcobo in the Eastern Cape. READ: Parliament slams CRL chair's comment on eNgcobo CRL chairwoman Thoko Mkhwanazi-Xaluva revealed the church – where a number of those accused of the murders were found hiding – was probed back in 2016. Five officers and a retired soldier were killed last week when a gang attacked the police station. Seven suspects were killed when police raided the church. eNCA